    • Method Detail

      • downloadFile

        File downloadFile(String filename)
           throws PbcsClientException
        Download a file that has been previously uploaded or otherwise exists from an export. Note that it's possible for a file to show on the application snapshot listing (such as provided by listFiles()) but not be able to download that file. This seems to be a quirk in the REST API such that folders themselves are considered files of type LCM.
        Parameters:
        filename - the name of the file, such as "export.txt"
        Returns:
        a File object with a handle to the downloaded file
        Throws:
        PbcsClientException - if there is an error retrieving the file (network, file doesn't exist)
